  "description": "Integrated fish and plant production system where fish waste provides nutrients for plants, and plants filter water for fish. Aquaponics uses natural biological nitrogen cycling (ammonia → nitrite → nitrate) without chemical pH adjustment, producing both fish protein and vegetables in a single recirculating system. Simpler and lower-tech than hydroponic pH control systems.",
